Package imp.core.exceptions

Contains the exceptions IMP may throw.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    TestIMPExceptions  
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    BodyNotFoundException
    Represents when a command is given to populate data on a nonexistent body.
    IMPArgumentException
    Represents an argument exception for the command line IMP.
    IMPException
    Represents a general IMP exception.
    IMPFileNotFoundException
    Represents a file not found exception within the IMP framework.
    IMPIllegalStateException
    Exception class used to indicate that something is in an invalid state.
    IMPRuntimeException
    A class to extend from so that we don't have to catch NullPointerExceptions
    InvalidDatatypeException
    Represents when a Contains method would return true, but for the wrong type of element i.e.
    InvalidParameterException
    Represents when the Command is passed in a parameter that is bad.
    InvalidTypeCastException
    Class to be thrown whenever someone tries to convert an expression value into something that it shouldn't be
    JointNotFoundException
    Represents when a command is given to populate data on a nonexistent joint.
    LoopException
    Exceptions dealing with loop finding.
    MatrixIndexOutOfBoundsException
    Represents an exception when the user attempts to manipulate a value from a matrix that does not exist or is denied access to.
    NameConflictException
    Represents an exception when an element is added to a model that already contains an element by that name.
    NonExistentJointEntry
    Thrown when an attempt to retrieve a JointBuilder from the DynamicJointBuilder that doesn't exist
    NullParameterException
    Represents an exception when the user attempts to pass a null value to a parameter.
    ParserRecognitionError
    Represents an exception with the parser.
    SavingException
    Represents an exception when the IMP model is being saved.
    SelfLoopException
    Represents an exception when two bodies form an enclosed loop.
    ShaderException
    Exceptions dealing with OpenGL Shaders.
    WrappedException
    An unknown exception caught by IMP
